{"id":929050,"xmlId":"com.jetbrains.restClient","name":"HTTP Client","description":"Provides the ability to compose and execute HTTP requests from the code editor.<br><br>\n\n    The following features are available:\n    <ul>\n      <li>Coding assistance with completion, highlighting, folding, and inline documentation</li>\n      <li>Live templates</li>\n      <li>Environment and in-place variables</li>\n      <li>Response handling API</li>\n      <li>Import from Postman Collections and from cURL</li>\n      <li>Send gRPC, WebSocket, and GraphQL requests in addition to regular HTTP</li>\n      <li>Support for OAuth 2.0 authorization: authenticate using the built-in browser, get access tokens, and preview auth logs</li>\n    </ul>\n    See the <a>documentation</a> for details.\n<h2>Getting started</h2>\n<ol>\n  <li>\nCreate a file with the <i>.http</i> or <i>.rest</i> extension.\n  </li>\n  <li>\nIn the created file, use the <b>Add Request</b> editor shortcut link or compose the request manually.<br>\n  </li>\n  <li>\nClick the <b>Run</b> button in the gutter to run the request and view the received response.<br>\n  </li>\n  <li>\nUse the <b>Examples</b> editor shortcut link to explore the additional features and capabilities.<br>\n  </li>\n  <li>\nUse the <b>Open Log</b> editor shortcut link to get an overview of the 50 recently executed requests and rerun any of them.<br>\n  </li>\n</ol>","organization":"JetBrains s.r.o.","tags":["Web"],"version":"253.29346.270","dependencies":["intellij.json.backend","com.intellij.modules.lang","com.intellij.marketplace","intellij.regexp","com.intellij.modules.xml","com.intellij.platform.images","com.intellij.jsonpath","intellij.libraries.ktor.client.cio"],"optionalDependencies":["intellij.libraries.grpc.netty.shaded","intellij.restClient/intelliLang","intellij.libraries.grpc","idea.plugin.protoeditor","intellij.textmate","com.intellij.modules.json","com.intellij.microservices.ui","com.intellij.java","com.intellij.lang.jsgraphql"